WEBVTT

00:00.028 --> 00:03.083
[THE LUMINEERS'
"LIFE IN THE CITY" PLAYS]

00:04.365 --> 00:05.971
MEREDITH: Talking with a patient's family

00:05.997 --> 00:08.641
is a crash course
in grace under pressure.

00:08.642 --> 00:10.457
One clumsy word,

00:10.482 --> 00:12.263
one careless gesture,

00:12.288 --> 00:13.999
can cause irreparable harm.

00:14.024 --> 00:15.630
[SIGHING] Okay, hold on. You know what?

00:15.655 --> 00:18.687
I need to get a picture of her
in this cute little hat.

00:18.712 --> 00:20.457
Okay. Um.

00:20.482 --> 00:22.367
Oh, come on. Great.

00:22.392 --> 00:24.207
Camera's full. [CHUCKLES]

00:24.232 --> 00:25.770
You need to delete some pictures.

00:25.795 --> 00:27.298
No, I just need a bigger phone.

00:27.323 --> 00:28.444
- Okay?
- Yeah, okay. Hold on.

00:28.469 --> 00:29.676
Mwah!

00:29.676 --> 00:31.526
- Have a good day.
- Thank you. You, too.

00:31.550 --> 00:33.721
Ideally you're dealing
with a healthy family,

00:33.746 --> 00:37.012
where the main focus is on the
well-being of their loved one.

00:37.037 --> 00:39.153
But that is not often the case.

00:41.502 --> 00:42.856
[SIGHS]

00:42.881 --> 00:44.982
Hey, what are you doing
with that elephant?

00:45.007 --> 00:46.754
Uh... Uh Leo left it at day care,

00:46.779 --> 00:49.775
and I need to give it back to
Owen before he freaks out.

00:49.800 --> 00:51.025
It's his favorite. [CHUCKLES]

00:51.050 --> 00:53.741
We have three of them.
And that one's Ellis's.

00:53.741 --> 00:56.112
Owen doesn't know I'm pregnant.

00:56.137 --> 00:57.778
And I think I should probably tell him.

00:57.803 --> 00:59.028
Yeah. Probably.

00:59.053 --> 01:00.625
Unless, I mean...

01:00.650 --> 01:02.986
He has his own baby with another person.

01:03.011 --> 01:04.167
I mean, does it really matter?

01:04.191 --> 01:06.424
He will get it, eventually,

01:06.449 --> 01:08.796
when I'm huge and in labor and...

01:08.821 --> 01:10.946
Right. Well, let me know what you decide.
I can't be late.

01:13.207 --> 01:16.446
But a surgeon is required, above all,

01:16.471 --> 01:18.042
to tell the truth.

01:18.067 --> 01:19.501
[DOOR CLOSES]

01:19.526 --> 01:21.203
And the truth is messy.

01:21.228 --> 01:22.696
[INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS]

01:22.721 --> 01:23.952
- Catherine.
- Maggie.

01:23.953 --> 01:26.635
Hi! How is it being back?

01:26.660 --> 01:29.448
- Oh, it's good to be operating again.
- Yeah.

01:29.473 --> 01:33.581
Tell me, how are things
here with the restructuring?

01:33.606 --> 01:35.455
Uh, Tom Koracick is...

01:35.480 --> 01:38.259
- a... brilliant surgeon.
- [ELEVATOR BELL DINGS]

01:38.259 --> 01:40.178
Not everybody's cup of tea.

01:40.203 --> 01:42.713
I heard he and Jackson
really got into it.

01:42.738 --> 01:44.275
Oh, yeah, I wouldn't know.

01:44.300 --> 01:46.046
That boy can be so tight-lipped.

01:46.071 --> 01:47.366
He gets it from me.

01:47.391 --> 01:51.141
And I know that's hard
to live with at times.

01:51.142 --> 01:53.616
Have you and Jackson talked much lately?

01:53.641 --> 01:55.942
We should have dinner soon.

01:55.967 --> 01:57.609
The four of us.

01:57.634 --> 02:00.006
- I don't know if that's such a good... Oh.
- Oh, no excuses.

02:00.031 --> 02:01.985
Come on. Family's too important.

02:02.010 --> 02:03.547
- Yeah, okay.
- Mm.

02:03.572 --> 02:06.360
♪

02:06.385 --> 02:08.532
- [INDISTINCT CHATTER]
- [TELEPHONE RINGING]

02:08.533 --> 02:09.828
WOMAN: I'm looking forward to it.

02:09.853 --> 02:11.148
[WHISPERING] Me, too. Yeah.

02:11.173 --> 02:14.897
[INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS]

02:14.922 --> 02:16.842
Richard Webber, are you seriously

02:16.867 --> 02:19.342
just gonna walk on by me like that?

02:19.367 --> 02:21.807
I'm sorry about what happened
in the diner.

02:21.832 --> 02:24.272
- Let me make it up to you.
- I don't think so.

02:24.297 --> 02:27.224
Just coffee... I'll keep my distance.

02:27.249 --> 02:28.799
It's not a good idea.

02:29.679 --> 02:32.398
[FOOTSTEPS DEPARTING]

02:32.423 --> 02:34.401
Well, let's go ahead
and change her pain meds

02:34.402 --> 02:35.523
from I.V. to oral.

02:35.548 --> 02:38.022
- We need to talk.
- I am talking.

02:38.047 --> 02:39.342
To someone else.

02:39.367 --> 02:41.460
Sorry about that.
And check her drain output.

02:41.485 --> 02:43.946
If it's below 20 cc,
we can go ahead and remove it.

02:43.946 --> 02:45.483
Yes, you were saying?

02:45.508 --> 02:47.046
Your mother would like to have dinner.

02:47.071 --> 02:48.088
I know. She texted.

02:48.113 --> 02:49.569
She thinks we're still together.

02:50.257 --> 02:51.905
Oh. Yeah. "Oh."

02:52.578 --> 02:55.617
I take it you didn't say
anything to Richard, then?

02:55.937 --> 02:58.794
W-Well, I never see Richard
because he's, um...

02:58.819 --> 03:00.739
- he's been fired.
- And that's my fault, too?

03:00.764 --> 03:01.988
I-I'm having trouble

03:02.013 --> 03:03.733
- keeping track with you.
- You know what? It's fine.

03:03.734 --> 03:05.758
We can just tell them over dinner.
You should bring Vic.

03:05.783 --> 03:08.153
- That'd be fun.
- I should bring Vic.

03:08.178 --> 03:09.786
- Vic is fun.
- Ohh.

03:09.811 --> 03:11.765
Do you guys laugh a lot
when you talk about her fiancé

03:11.790 --> 03:13.293
who died 10 minutes bef...

03:13.318 --> 03:15.688
I wonder if you can help me.
I'm looking for Richard Webber.

03:15.713 --> 03:17.772
I'm sorry, does that woman look like me?

03:17.797 --> 03:20.331
I dunno. I'd have to see her scowl first.

03:20.331 --> 03:22.180
But he works here. I know it.

03:22.205 --> 03:23.431
Richard Webber.

03:23.456 --> 03:24.785
Can you check with someone?

03:24.810 --> 03:26.764
Take it easy, Sabi.
Don't wear yourself out.

03:26.789 --> 03:28.084
NURSE KAREN: Yeah, I know who he is,

03:28.109 --> 03:29.808
but he doesn't work here anymore.

03:29.809 --> 03:31.519
You need to go to
Pacific Northwest General.

03:31.544 --> 03:33.325
I'm sorry, I couldn't help but overhear.

03:33.350 --> 03:34.784
Are you looking for Richard Webber?

03:34.809 --> 03:36.693
Oh, my God, it's you!

03:36.718 --> 03:37.977
Maggie!

03:38.002 --> 03:39.393
Oh! [CHUCKLES]

03:39.394 --> 03:41.348
I can't believe it.

03:41.373 --> 03:42.667
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

03:42.692 --> 03:44.229
And who am I now?

03:44.254 --> 03:45.792
Oh, sorry. I-I...

03:45.817 --> 03:47.320
I'm Sabrina.

03:47.345 --> 03:50.063
But everyone calls me Sabi.
Rhymes with "baby."

03:50.088 --> 03:52.355
And this is my dad, Chris.

03:52.379 --> 03:53.681
♪

03:53.681 --> 03:55.530
I-I'm sorry, I'm still confused.

03:55.555 --> 03:58.377
I... I'm Sabrina Webber.

03:58.402 --> 04:00.357
Richard's my uncle.

04:00.382 --> 04:02.105
And he's your biological father.

04:02.105 --> 04:03.425
So...

04:03.450 --> 04:05.413
we're your family!

04:05.438 --> 04:08.920
- [LAUGHS]
- [EXHALES SHARPLY]

04:08.945 --> 04:15.466
Synced & corrected by -robtor-
www.addic7ed.com

04:15.634 --> 04:16.928
[HORN HONKS]

04:16.954 --> 04:19.706
And I am not a big crier,
but I'm telling to you,

04:19.731 --> 04:21.130
I cried for days.

04:21.154 --> 04:23.109
I mean, that poor little hamster.

04:23.134 --> 04:25.762
Long story short... never buy
a pet on Craigslist.

04:25.763 --> 04:27.717
You wanna see a picture? It's gross.

04:27.742 --> 04:29.418
- You'll love it.
- Oh, oh, no, thank you.

04:29.443 --> 04:31.120
[CHUCKLES]

04:31.145 --> 04:33.411
So, Uncle Richard got fired?

04:33.436 --> 04:34.731
- What happened?
- [SIGHS]

04:34.756 --> 04:35.986
It's a long story.

04:35.987 --> 04:37.281
Drinking again?

04:37.306 --> 04:39.191
What? No, no.

04:39.216 --> 04:41.136
It was a-a bureaucratic matter.

04:41.161 --> 04:42.837
"Bureaucratic matter"?

04:42.862 --> 04:44.732
So there's a really long story.

04:44.733 --> 04:45.992
[SABRINA AND MAGGIE CHUCKLE]

04:46.017 --> 04:48.978
So you're, like, a super genius, right?

04:49.003 --> 04:50.750
I mean, well, that's what
all the articles say.

04:50.775 --> 04:51.860
[STAMMERS]

04:51.885 --> 04:54.221
I'm sorry, this is j... It's so weird.

04:54.246 --> 04:55.784
You know so much about me,

04:55.809 --> 04:58.568
and I know almost nothing about you.

04:58.569 --> 05:01.147
Not a surprise. Richard's ashamed of us.

05:01.172 --> 05:02.293
- What?
- [SCOFFS]

05:02.318 --> 05:03.926
No, that can't be true.

05:03.951 --> 05:05.957
Only you've never talked to us,

05:05.958 --> 05:07.426
never met us, never even heard of us.

05:07.451 --> 05:08.746
Yeah, d-don't mind him.

05:08.771 --> 05:09.891
He's a grump.

05:09.916 --> 05:12.044
Uncle Richard called us a while back,

05:12.069 --> 05:13.398
after your podcast,

05:13.423 --> 05:15.216
explained the whole secret affair thing.

05:15.217 --> 05:16.997
Then I read all about you.

05:17.022 --> 05:18.421
Made sense, too.

05:18.446 --> 05:20.990
Genius is in our blood.

05:21.015 --> 05:23.572
You know I got into Stanford. Uh-huh...

05:23.573 --> 05:25.596
Woulda gone, too, except in-state tuition

05:25.621 --> 05:27.853
- is a whole lot cheaper.
- Yeah, yeah.

05:27.878 --> 05:30.110
I'm sorry, this is just so weird!

05:30.135 --> 05:32.505
I mean, we look the same,
sound the same...

05:32.530 --> 05:33.825
We could be twins!

05:33.850 --> 05:35.804
Well, twins, no...
I mean, we're genetically...

05:35.829 --> 05:36.916
- we're more... Oh. [CHUCKLES]
- [SHUTTER CLICKS]

05:36.941 --> 05:38.825
...akin to...

05:38.850 --> 05:42.471
- [GASPS, CHUCKLES]
- Well, that's... that's weird.

05:42.496 --> 05:44.069
WOMAN ON P.A.: Mary Griggs to L&D.

05:44.094 --> 05:47.391
Mary Griggs to L&D.

05:47.392 --> 05:48.790
- Owen.
- Yeah.

05:48.815 --> 05:50.248
A... Amelia. Everything okay?

05:50.273 --> 05:51.290
[EXHALES SHARPLY] Fine.

05:51.315 --> 05:53.628
Uh, great, actually. Um...

05:54.092 --> 05:57.679
I just wanted to, uh...
to give this back to Leo.

05:57.704 --> 05:59.847
Oh, well, thanks,
but I don't think this is...

05:59.848 --> 06:01.373
Link and I are having a baby.

06:03.423 --> 06:04.857
[QUIETLY] Wow. Um... okay.

06:04.882 --> 06:06.211
And you need to know.

06:06.236 --> 06:07.843
Well, I want Leo
to be in the baby's life.

06:07.868 --> 06:10.552
He's already such a good big
brother to Allison, and I...

06:10.577 --> 06:12.253
I'm...[CHUCKLES] realizing in this moment

06:12.278 --> 06:15.114
that we've gone from zero to
three babies in 60 seconds.

06:15.114 --> 06:18.041
So... yay for all the babies!

06:18.066 --> 06:21.999
- Incoming!
- Cassidy Gardner, 25, GCS 14,

06:22.024 --> 06:23.909
blunt trauma to the abdomen, arm lac.

06:23.934 --> 06:25.436
Hemodynamically stable.

06:25.461 --> 06:26.478
[BREATHING QUICKLY]

06:26.503 --> 06:27.797
Okay, what happened?

06:27.822 --> 06:29.423
I fell down the stairs. I just fell.

06:29.424 --> 06:30.996
Her son called 911.

06:31.021 --> 06:32.940
Henry, Mommy's gonna be fine.

06:32.965 --> 06:34.503
You did real good, buddy.

06:34.528 --> 06:36.936
So someone's gonna sit with you
until we take care of your mom, okay?

06:36.937 --> 06:38.127
I got him.

06:38.152 --> 06:40.037
- I need the practice.
- Thanks.

06:40.062 --> 06:41.148
Okay, let's go.

06:41.173 --> 06:43.509
We need chest and pelvic X-rays now.

06:43.534 --> 06:46.843
- [INDISTINCT CHATTER]
- [FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

06:46.868 --> 06:48.023
[TELEPHONE RINGS IN DISTANCE]

06:48.048 --> 06:50.558
Uncle Richard! [CHUCKLES]

06:50.583 --> 06:52.329
Oh! Sabi?

06:52.354 --> 06:54.047
- What... What are you...
- [CHUCKLES]

06:54.047 --> 06:56.244
Maggie? Chris? W-W-What's going on?

06:56.269 --> 06:58.223
They were looking for you at Grey-Sloan.

06:58.248 --> 07:00.445
- It's so good to see you, Uncle Richard!
- Oh, my gosh.

07:00.446 --> 07:02.956
We missed you at Christmas.
And Thanksgiving.

07:02.981 --> 07:05.525
And Easter and birthdays
and family reunions.

07:05.550 --> 07:06.885
I-I-I know. It's, uh,

07:06.910 --> 07:08.338
- been a tough year.
- [SIGHS]

07:08.363 --> 07:10.080
Has it been a tough five years?

07:10.797 --> 07:13.272
- Anyway, hi!
- [LAUGHS]

07:13.297 --> 07:15.008
Hi. [GRUNTS]

07:15.033 --> 07:16.987
Well... Well, um...

07:17.012 --> 07:18.273
Welcome to Pac North.

07:18.298 --> 07:19.974
Um, you want the tour?

07:19.999 --> 07:21.328
[CHUCKLES] Well, that sounds like fun,

07:21.353 --> 07:23.550
but maybe in a minute.
I'm kinda worn out.

07:23.575 --> 07:25.456
Okay, sweetie, take it easy.

07:25.456 --> 07:28.174
And I need you look at something first...

07:28.199 --> 07:30.152
I don't think he needs
to see a dead hamster.

07:30.177 --> 07:31.299
[LAUGHS] No.

07:31.324 --> 07:32.827
It's even grosser than that.

07:32.852 --> 07:35.222
Oh, okay. [CHUCKLES]

07:35.247 --> 07:36.784
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

07:36.809 --> 07:38.486
♪

07:38.511 --> 07:39.971
MAGGIE: [GASPS]

07:39.971 --> 07:42.098
Why are you showing us a picture

07:42.123 --> 07:44.622
of an insanely large biatrial myxoma?

07:45.491 --> 07:46.786
Because it's mine.

07:46.811 --> 07:50.629
♪

07:53.794 --> 07:55.368
You haven't had any other symptoms?

07:55.393 --> 07:57.104
Some swelling in my legs.

07:57.129 --> 07:59.361
Um, and I lose my breath sometimes

07:59.386 --> 08:01.096
when I walk my dog.

08:01.121 --> 08:02.694
These scans are three weeks old.

08:02.719 --> 08:04.707
Why did you wait so long to come?

08:04.732 --> 08:06.339
My doctor said it could be some time

08:06.364 --> 08:07.902
before it got really bad.

08:07.927 --> 08:10.389
And news like this,
it takes a minute to process.

08:10.389 --> 08:12.379
And Dad wanted to go up to Chicago,

08:12.404 --> 08:14.462
but I wanted to come here.

08:14.487 --> 08:16.024
I'm glad you agreed.

08:16.049 --> 08:17.897
I didn't want her traveling alone.

08:18.547 --> 08:19.738
Okay, Sabrina, this kind of...

08:19.763 --> 08:23.217
- Sabi, please.
- Okay. Sabi.

08:23.217 --> 08:24.963
This kind of tumor is operable,

08:24.988 --> 08:26.873
but it can grow really rapidly,

08:26.898 --> 08:29.222
so we need to get
some new imaging right away.

08:30.589 --> 08:32.995
It was really dumb of me
to wait, wasn't it?

08:33.020 --> 08:35.903
♪

08:35.928 --> 08:37.744
Let's, uh... Let's go get those scans.

08:37.769 --> 08:42.419
♪

08:42.419 --> 08:44.408
Was your dad home when your mom fell?

08:44.433 --> 08:46.318
I don't have a dad.

08:46.343 --> 08:48.193
I came home from school on the bus,

08:48.218 --> 08:52.490
and Mom was in the basement
o-o-on the floor.

08:52.608 --> 08:54.735
She couldn't move.

08:54.760 --> 08:56.124
Is she gonna be okay?

08:56.149 --> 08:58.208
She has got a really great
team of doctors

08:58.233 --> 09:00.153
taking care of her.

09:00.178 --> 09:01.715
Here.

09:01.740 --> 09:03.972
Maybe holding this guy
will make you feel better.

09:03.997 --> 09:07.241
♪

09:07.241 --> 09:09.612
I'm so sorry about this wait.
Do you want to sit down?

09:09.637 --> 09:11.144
No, no. I'm okay now.

09:11.145 --> 09:12.301
Minute you start acting sick,

09:12.326 --> 09:14.454
that's when you really get sick.

09:15.207 --> 09:16.606
So...

09:16.631 --> 09:17.879
what's the tea?

09:19.974 --> 09:21.998
- You know what tea is, right?
- Yeah, no, I do.

09:22.023 --> 09:23.733
I just, uh...

09:23.758 --> 09:24.878
I mostly work. [CHUCKLES]

09:24.903 --> 09:27.280
There's nothing? No scandal?

09:27.280 --> 09:28.679
No love life?!

09:28.704 --> 09:31.629
Uh, my ex-boyfriend rebounded
with a firefighter?

09:31.654 --> 09:32.809
Gay?

09:32.834 --> 09:34.650
Hot chick.

09:34.675 --> 09:36.490
Okay, then. I hate him.

09:36.515 --> 09:37.702
[LAUGHS]

09:37.727 --> 09:39.716
- We're family. I've got you.
- [LAUGHS]

09:39.741 --> 09:42.459
I hope he wakes up tomorrow,
realizes what a mistake he made,

09:42.484 --> 09:45.152
but it's too late because
you're with Idris Elba.

09:45.177 --> 09:46.715
[LAUGHS] Oh, girl.

09:46.740 --> 09:48.208
- Mm-hmm!
- [BOTH LAUGHING]

09:48.233 --> 09:50.048
Girl, gimme your phone.
You need my number.

09:50.073 --> 09:53.034
- [CHUCKLES]
- [LAUGHS]

09:53.059 --> 09:54.412
- Here.
- [LAUGHS]

09:54.437 --> 09:56.252
Mm.

09:56.277 --> 09:58.161
Hey, do you like crossword puzzles?

09:58.186 --> 09:59.273
Love 'em.

09:59.298 --> 10:00.843
Acrostics, Sudoku,

10:00.868 --> 10:02.128
but crosswords are the best.

10:02.150 --> 10:03.618
I only do the ones
on the weekends, though,

10:03.643 --> 10:05.701
- because the other ones are...
- TOGETHER: ...too easy.

10:05.726 --> 10:08.617
- Right?! I get so bored!
- [LAUGHING] I know.

10:08.642 --> 10:11.429
We have so much shared DNA,
I bet we have a ton in common.

10:11.476 --> 10:12.944
- Do you like classical music?
- Love it.

10:12.969 --> 10:14.472
- Can you whistle?
- Yes!

10:14.497 --> 10:16.538
I know that's not necessarily,
like, a genetic thing...

10:16.563 --> 10:18.916
Um they're, uh... they're ready for you.

10:18.941 --> 10:20.817
[INHALES DEEPLY] Okay.

10:20.842 --> 10:23.038
- To be continued... Cuz!
- Yeah.

10:23.063 --> 10:25.582
[MAGGIE AND SABRINA LAUGH]

10:25.607 --> 10:27.492
[CHUCKLES]

10:27.517 --> 10:31.971
♪

10:31.996 --> 10:33.117
[DOOR CLOSES]

10:33.142 --> 10:35.131
[CELLPHONE VIBRATES]

10:35.156 --> 10:41.761
♪

10:41.761 --> 10:43.542
This thing smells new.

10:43.567 --> 10:45.712
Am I the first person in it?

10:45.836 --> 10:47.131
Close to it.

10:47.156 --> 10:48.277
Hold still now.

10:48.302 --> 10:49.700
[SCANNER WHIRRING]

10:49.725 --> 10:52.302
I can't imagine how strange
this must be for you.

10:52.727 --> 10:55.488
- I'm sorry I didn't tell you...
- Oh, are you kidding?!

10:55.706 --> 10:57.555
It is fascinating.

10:57.580 --> 10:59.986
And, yes, it's really, really strange.

11:00.011 --> 11:02.912
I've never had a relative
who looked like me before.

11:03.611 --> 11:06.781
And she's just been out there
practically my entire life,

11:06.806 --> 11:08.746
- just having different experiences.
- [CHUCKLES]

11:08.771 --> 11:11.211
I wonder if we've ever been
in the same town

11:11.236 --> 11:13.051
at the same time before today.

11:13.076 --> 11:15.586
I was in Dayton once.
I had a long layover.

11:15.611 --> 11:17.114
I went to the mall.

11:17.139 --> 11:20.121
Has it really been five years
since you saw each other?

11:21.268 --> 11:23.041
Uh... Sabi's not like the others.

11:23.315 --> 11:26.211
My brother and sister
always resented me for leaving,

11:26.494 --> 11:28.691
resented my success.

11:28.716 --> 11:30.778
Accused me of putting on airs

11:30.803 --> 11:32.509
and acting like I was better.

11:34.158 --> 11:37.180
Adele always had a way
of smoothing things over.

11:37.205 --> 11:39.390
I should've tried harder after she died.

11:41.533 --> 11:44.020
And they didn't know about me
until the podcast.

11:44.963 --> 11:46.812
When I called to tell them, they, uh,

11:46.837 --> 11:48.244
said some vicious things,

11:48.244 --> 11:51.796
and I think I just wanted
to protect you from that.

11:51.821 --> 11:53.255
[BREATHES SHARPLY]

11:53.280 --> 11:54.609
But it's, uh,

11:54.634 --> 11:56.726
it's nice to see the two of you
get along so well.

11:56.751 --> 11:58.492
[BEEPS]

11:58.493 --> 11:59.995
Oh, God.

12:00.020 --> 12:02.113
The tumor's reaching up through
the tricuspid valve

12:02.138 --> 12:03.814
and into her pulmonary artery now.

12:03.839 --> 12:05.264
I think it's doubled in size.

12:05.264 --> 12:07.774
This might be the biggest
heart tumor I have ever seen.

12:07.799 --> 12:10.690
Is somebody gonna get me out
of this thing or what?

12:10.715 --> 12:13.961
♪

12:13.961 --> 12:17.269
FAST exam shows the free fluid
on the perisplenic space.

12:17.294 --> 12:20.448
Ma'am, did you have any
symptoms before you fell?

12:20.479 --> 12:22.226
I-I was bringing the laundry upstairs,

12:22.250 --> 12:23.371
and I got really dizzy.

12:23.396 --> 12:25.364
Uh-huh. Wait, you see that?

12:25.993 --> 12:27.115
Excess fluid?

12:27.140 --> 12:28.989
That's a heartbeat. [INHALES DEEPLY]

12:29.014 --> 12:30.066
Ma'am...

12:31.083 --> 12:34.044
Ma'am, did you know
that you were pregnant?

12:34.069 --> 12:35.571
Was or am?

12:35.596 --> 12:37.412
[HEART BEATING]

12:37.437 --> 12:38.890
We have a strong heartbeat.
Your baby's okay.

12:38.915 --> 12:40.349
Okay?

12:40.374 --> 12:42.363
[WHISPERING] It didn't work.

12:42.388 --> 12:43.682
What... What didn't?

12:43.707 --> 12:45.556
I can't have another baby.

12:45.581 --> 12:46.980
I can't.

12:47.005 --> 12:48.890
[BREATHES SHAKILY]

12:48.915 --> 12:50.510
[HEAT BEATING]

12:52.190 --> 12:54.744
WOMAN ON P.A.: Jeanette
Brody to Admitting.

12:54.769 --> 12:56.359
Jeanette Brody to Admitting.

12:57.849 --> 12:59.730
- Hey. Hey.
- Hey.

12:59.755 --> 13:00.806
How's Mom?

13:00.831 --> 13:02.140
She's, um...

13:02.880 --> 13:05.389
[WHISPERING] Listen,
her fall wasn't an accident.

13:05.414 --> 13:07.687
She was trying to terminate a pregnancy.

13:08.913 --> 13:10.694
By throwing herself down the stairs?

13:10.719 --> 13:12.257
I don't know. She's not talking much...

13:12.282 --> 13:13.680
Well, do you want me to try?

13:13.705 --> 13:15.312
She might be more comfortable
talking to another woman.

13:15.337 --> 13:16.388
I can say it's a neuro check.

13:16.413 --> 13:17.847
Sure, might help.

13:17.872 --> 13:19.061
I already paged psych,

13:19.086 --> 13:20.555
but they take forever around here, so...

13:20.580 --> 13:23.159
- How pregnant is she?
- 8, 10 weeks. I'm not sure.

13:23.184 --> 13:24.340
Uh, if you're not up to this,

13:24.365 --> 13:26.319
then I can get someone else, you know.

13:26.344 --> 13:27.847
Why wouldn't I feel up to it?

13:27.872 --> 13:29.188
[TELEPHONE RINGING IN DISTANCE]

13:29.196 --> 13:30.733
Because I'm all knocked up?

13:30.758 --> 13:32.156
- [SCOFFS]
- It's okay, Owen.

13:32.181 --> 13:33.303
I don't need a fainting couch.

13:33.328 --> 13:34.831
I will be fine.

13:34.856 --> 13:36.462
Yeah, okay. Thank you.

13:36.487 --> 13:37.908
[TELEPHONE RINGS IN DISTANCE]

13:37.908 --> 13:38.890
[BEEPING]

13:38.915 --> 13:41.494
- That's the same tumor?
- Yes.

13:41.519 --> 13:44.104
And now it's extending
into your pulmonary artery.

13:44.104 --> 13:46.650
Looks kinda like a baby swan
with that little neck.

13:46.675 --> 13:48.281
- [LAUGHS]
- Sabi...

13:48.306 --> 13:50.191
this tumor isn't stable.

13:50.216 --> 13:52.136
It could stop your heart's
ability to pump blood.

13:52.161 --> 13:53.941
We need to get you up to surgery.

13:53.966 --> 13:55.191
Today.

13:55.216 --> 13:57.483
- Well, who's gonna do it?
- You're in luck.

13:57.508 --> 13:59.844
This happens to be my specialty.

13:59.869 --> 14:01.893
You? But you don't work here.

14:01.918 --> 14:03.941
They granted me privileges,
so we're good to go.

14:03.966 --> 14:05.271
SABI: But we're family.

14:05.272 --> 14:07.122
And we're basically twins.

14:07.147 --> 14:09.309
I mean, What if you see me lying
on that operating table,

14:09.334 --> 14:11.810
and you freak out because
it's you on the table?

14:11.835 --> 14:13.372
MAGGIE: That is not a thing I do.

14:13.397 --> 14:15.977
And I'm the best.

14:16.002 --> 14:17.574
Then get second best.

14:17.599 --> 14:20.360
Sabi, she won't even be able
to see your face.

14:20.361 --> 14:21.689
It's covered during surgery.

14:21.714 --> 14:24.294
Okay, that is really creepy.
Do people know that?

14:24.319 --> 14:26.516
I-Isn't there a law
against operating on family?

14:26.541 --> 14:28.229
It isn't a law. It's a guideline.

14:28.230 --> 14:30.774
And since we've only known
each other about two hours,

14:30.799 --> 14:33.830
I'm not really sure how it applies here.

14:33.855 --> 14:36.296
Apple doesn't fall too far from the tree.

14:36.321 --> 14:37.953
- Excuse me?
- You're steamrolling her,

14:37.978 --> 14:39.039
thinking you know what's best.

14:39.064 --> 14:40.948
You're not even listening
to her concerns.

14:40.973 --> 14:42.656
I'm listening. They're just not valid.

14:42.656 --> 14:44.576
Not valid?

14:44.601 --> 14:47.319
We look alike,
we have some things in common,

14:47.344 --> 14:49.541
but we're... we're not family.

14:49.566 --> 14:51.098
Not in the way that matters.

14:51.098 --> 14:53.956
I am the best cardiothoracic
surgeon in the Northwest.

14:53.981 --> 14:56.595
I run my department. I innovate.

14:56.620 --> 14:58.226
You want me in that room.

14:58.251 --> 14:59.962
What makes you think
you know what she wants?

14:59.987 --> 15:02.658
- You don't even know her.
- Which is why I can do this!

15:04.141 --> 15:06.789
Richard? A little support, please?

15:06.814 --> 15:08.421
Um... you know,

15:08.446 --> 15:10.540
I don't trust the cardio surgeon
who's here today.

15:10.565 --> 15:11.720
Thank you.

15:11.745 --> 15:13.621
So I am your only option.

15:13.646 --> 15:14.906
But, um...

15:14.931 --> 15:18.443
there is an on-call surgeon
who's quite good.

15:19.202 --> 15:21.468
I'll, um... I'll make a call.

15:21.493 --> 15:22.822
Thank you.

15:22.847 --> 15:24.323
Took you long enough.

15:24.830 --> 15:26.263
[SIGHS]

15:26.288 --> 15:32.270
♪

15:32.295 --> 15:34.709
[SIGHS]

15:35.040 --> 15:36.419
Maggie.

15:37.976 --> 15:40.694
Um, will you, uh, stick around
and brief the surgeon?

15:40.719 --> 15:42.222
Maybe consult?

15:42.247 --> 15:44.548
You want me to consult for
someone who's not as good as me

15:44.573 --> 15:46.319
instead of giving your niece
the best shot she's got?

15:46.344 --> 15:47.951
[SIGHS] Maggie, they're family.

15:47.976 --> 15:49.478
So you're just gonna agree with them

15:49.503 --> 15:51.666
because of some bad history
with your brother?

15:51.691 --> 15:54.062
No, that's not what I meant.

15:54.087 --> 15:55.788
Look, they're your family, too.

15:55.813 --> 15:58.185
I know you just met
and it may not feel that way,

15:58.210 --> 15:59.920
but they... look, one day, it could.

15:59.945 --> 16:02.587
And God forbid something
goes wrong in the OR and...

16:02.612 --> 16:04.878
I'll always be the love child
who killed your favorite niece?

16:04.903 --> 16:06.372
Oh, come on, now.

16:06.397 --> 16:08.509
You'll never get a chance to know them.

16:08.534 --> 16:10.071
And I never would've known they existed

16:10.096 --> 16:11.808
if they hadn't come here.

16:11.833 --> 16:15.661
Richard, your niece came here
for help as a doctor.

16:15.686 --> 16:19.504
It's too bad you can't do her
the favor of thinking like one.

16:19.529 --> 16:21.241
Yes, I'll consult.

16:21.266 --> 16:22.722
Text me when he's here.

16:24.244 --> 16:27.831
[MONITOR BEEPING]

16:28.809 --> 16:31.388
No sign of concussion.

16:31.606 --> 16:32.970
How's Henry? Is he scared?

16:32.995 --> 16:34.844
Henry is over the moon.

16:34.869 --> 16:37.705
A very sweet nurse showed him
the snack drawer.

16:37.730 --> 16:38.957
OWEN: Cassidy, the CT shows

16:38.957 --> 16:40.772
that there is some bleeding
in your spleen.

16:40.797 --> 16:42.578
We're gonna have to take you up
to the OR to remove it,

16:42.603 --> 16:44.453
and I can do that laparoscopically.

16:44.478 --> 16:46.298
I-I don't have insurance right now.

16:46.299 --> 16:47.732
Henry just qualified for a state program,

16:47.757 --> 16:49.051
but I'm still waiting to hear.

16:49.076 --> 16:50.961
Emergency departments
don't turn people away,

16:50.986 --> 16:52.732
regardless of their financial situation,

16:52.757 --> 16:54.850
so they will give you the
surgery that you need, okay?

16:54.875 --> 16:58.844
[INHALES DEEPLY] But surgery, uh,

16:58.869 --> 17:01.551
will put the fetus at risk,
so, I have to ask you...

17:01.576 --> 17:03.340
Are you planning on keeping
this pregnancy?

17:03.341 --> 17:05.087
I love Henry.

17:05.112 --> 17:06.406
But it's a lot.

17:06.431 --> 17:08.003
I already work at two restaurants,

17:08.029 --> 17:09.948
and they try to give me
a flexible schedule,

17:09.973 --> 17:12.290
but there's only so much
that they can do.

17:12.290 --> 17:14.071
And another kid...
I mean, that's way more money,

17:14.097 --> 17:16.815
and... and even more time
away from Henry.

17:16.839 --> 17:19.662
I can't... I can't and I don't want to.

17:19.686 --> 17:21.503
So you threw yourself down the stairs?

17:21.503 --> 17:23.286
What?! Oh, my God, no!

17:23.310 --> 17:25.577
No, I tried to go to a clinic
that had financial assistance

17:25.602 --> 17:26.862
three times,

17:26.887 --> 17:28.181
but something always fell through.

17:28.205 --> 17:30.716
Henry got sick
or no one could sub for me.

17:30.741 --> 17:31.981
I-I ran out of favors.

17:31.981 --> 17:33.936
So I looked online, and I found this herb

17:33.961 --> 17:35.151
that was supposed to work.

17:35.176 --> 17:37.582
I-I doubled the recipe
to make sure it would work,

17:37.607 --> 17:39.457
but it made me dizzy.

17:39.482 --> 17:40.985
And then I fell.

17:41.010 --> 17:42.295
I just fell.

17:43.278 --> 17:45.198
I love my son.

17:45.223 --> 17:48.496
And I would never do anything
to try to hurt myself.

17:48.521 --> 17:50.844
I would never do anything
to try to hurt him.

17:50.869 --> 17:52.232
Okay, Cassidy, listen.

17:52.257 --> 17:53.598
You are okay right now.

17:53.923 --> 17:55.658
And Henry is okay.

17:55.708 --> 17:58.739
And if you want an abortion,
Dr. Hunt can get someone from OB

17:58.764 --> 18:00.267
to do that during your surgery

18:00.292 --> 18:02.836
once the bleeding in your
abdomen is under control.

18:02.861 --> 18:04.260
Oh, God, really?

18:04.285 --> 18:05.510
Thank you.

18:05.535 --> 18:07.078
- Thank you so much...
- Um, actually, Cassidy,

18:07.078 --> 18:09.276
I think we want to focus on
the fall injuries first.

18:09.301 --> 18:10.872
Okay?

18:10.897 --> 18:12.157
We can address the pregnancy

18:12.182 --> 18:14.241
once we know that you're all right.

18:14.266 --> 18:16.186
Oh. Okay.

18:16.211 --> 18:19.519
Okay, so, we'll see you up
in the OR shortly.

18:19.544 --> 18:23.130
♪

18:23.155 --> 18:26.533
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

18:26.558 --> 18:28.164
- What are you doing?
- You really overstepped in there.

18:28.189 --> 18:29.962
I'm a trauma surgeon.
I don't order abortions.

18:29.962 --> 18:31.986
You would have if the fetus
hadn't survived.

18:32.011 --> 18:33.525
But it did.

18:33.526 --> 18:36.279
Owen, she's eight weeks.
She doesn't need a full D&C.

18:36.304 --> 18:37.667
Exactly. It's not emergent,

18:37.692 --> 18:39.265
but her internal injuries are.

18:39.290 --> 18:41.912
So I'm gonna deal with those,
and then she can go see an OB.

18:42.254 --> 18:44.034
She seems pretty clear in her thinking

18:44.059 --> 18:45.354
and committed to her plan.

18:45.379 --> 18:47.645
Why not just give her
the help she's asking for?

18:47.670 --> 18:49.035
Thank you, Amelia, for your consult,

18:49.060 --> 18:50.529
but I'm gonna take it from here, okay?

18:50.554 --> 18:51.975
♪

18:57.215 --> 18:59.215
- [SIREN WAILS IN DISTANCE]
- [INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS]

18:59.215 --> 19:00.414
Hey.

19:01.299 --> 19:03.169
- What are you doing here?
- In the neighborhood.

19:03.170 --> 19:05.263
Lunch break. Having coffee with Alex.

19:05.287 --> 19:07.647
What are you doing in enemy territory?

19:09.072 --> 19:11.200
Wow. That's a beautiful tumor.

19:11.225 --> 19:12.694
Are you taking this out?

19:12.719 --> 19:14.160
[SCOFFS] I wish, but, no.

19:14.160 --> 19:15.698
I can't do it.

19:15.723 --> 19:17.295
Is it too risky?

19:17.320 --> 19:19.240
Please. I would destroy that thing.

19:19.264 --> 19:22.979
No, I can't do it because
it belongs to Richard's niece.

19:23.639 --> 19:24.834
And she doesn't want me to.

19:24.834 --> 19:26.753
We look so much alike we could be twins,

19:26.778 --> 19:28.698
which is, you know, surreal,

19:28.723 --> 19:30.782
but it's not more than I can handle.

19:30.807 --> 19:33.658
But she thinks it would be like
getting cut into by herself.

19:33.659 --> 19:35.509
I had a dream like that once.

19:35.534 --> 19:38.356
- Not good.
- What are we all doing here?

19:38.381 --> 19:39.606
- Alex.
- Patient.

19:39.631 --> 19:41.038
What patient?

19:42.687 --> 19:45.266
- Sexy.
- Yeah, I know.

19:45.291 --> 19:46.863
I told Owen about the baby.

19:46.888 --> 19:49.190
Oh, that's why you're here.
I thought you were defecting.

19:49.215 --> 19:51.888
I told him about the baby,
and he got weird.

19:51.889 --> 19:54.051
That's understandable.

19:54.076 --> 19:55.475
Is it?

19:55.500 --> 19:59.155
I mean, he's with Teddy, and he's happy.

19:59.180 --> 20:00.857
And just now, he just seemed like

20:00.882 --> 20:03.669
he was angry with me for being pregnant.

20:03.694 --> 20:04.955
But he's gotta get with the program.

20:04.980 --> 20:07.191
This kid is gonna be Leo's
little brother or sister.

20:07.191 --> 20:10.083
So he and Teddy are gonna be...

20:10.108 --> 20:11.680
aunt and uncle, I guess?

20:11.705 --> 20:13.590
Does Leo call Teddy "Mom"?

20:13.615 --> 20:15.812
No, no, he calls her "Weddy"

20:15.837 --> 20:17.742
because he's working on his T's.

20:18.580 --> 20:20.222
Oh, I get the question.

20:20.247 --> 20:23.092
Uh, I'm... Auntie Amelia.

20:23.093 --> 20:24.942
Betty's more like big sister.

20:24.967 --> 20:28.345
So Teddy's... stepmom, I guess?

20:28.370 --> 20:31.725
[PAGER RINGING, CELLPHONE VIBRATES]

20:31.725 --> 20:32.742
Damn it.

20:32.767 --> 20:34.721
Sabi's crashing. Here.

20:34.746 --> 20:36.874
[SIREN WAILING]

20:36.899 --> 20:38.541
Sabi is...?

20:38.566 --> 20:41.265
Her patient. And Richard's niece.

20:41.795 --> 20:43.923
- Oh, damn.
- Yeah.

20:43.948 --> 20:45.419
[WAILING CONTINUES]

20:45.419 --> 20:48.064
You know, Owen can be pissed
at me... I don't care...

20:48.718 --> 20:50.566
but he can't take it out on a patient.

20:51.780 --> 20:52.866
Do you want any...?

20:52.891 --> 20:54.671
[WAILING CONTINUES]

20:54.696 --> 20:56.442
Everybody's got a patient.

20:56.467 --> 20:57.623
I want a patient.

20:57.648 --> 20:59.116
- [ALARMS BLARING]
- What happened?

20:59.141 --> 21:00.401
She just stopped talking...

21:00.426 --> 21:01.963
She went into respiratory distress.

21:01.988 --> 21:04.463
- I had to intubate.
- [BLARING CONTINUES]

21:04.488 --> 21:06.432
The tumor is obstructing
blood flow to her lungs.

21:06.457 --> 21:08.515
Let's push fluids and start pressors.

21:08.540 --> 21:10.519
- Where's my sub?
- He's in the parking lot.

21:10.544 --> 21:12.568
But I didn't want him operating.

21:12.593 --> 21:13.853
This is all you.

21:13.878 --> 21:15.381
I'm glad you came to your senses.

21:15.406 --> 21:17.395
Prep an OR! Let's get her ready to move!

21:17.420 --> 21:18.992
Wait. I didn't say you could.

21:19.017 --> 21:20.207
You're not supposed to operate.

21:20.232 --> 21:21.943
I haven't even talked
to the other doctor.

21:21.968 --> 21:23.992
I know you say I always think
I know what's best.

21:24.017 --> 21:25.726
Well, in this case, I do.

21:26.834 --> 21:28.961
I know Margaret Pierce.

21:28.986 --> 21:30.663
And there's not a surgeon in this city

21:30.688 --> 21:33.337
with half of her skill and expertise.

21:33.362 --> 21:35.489
Chris, please.

21:35.514 --> 21:38.545
Don't put your daughter's life
in someone else's hands.

21:38.570 --> 21:41.717
♪

21:41.742 --> 21:45.137
- Thank you.
- I'm sorry. I should've said it sooner.

21:45.741 --> 21:47.522
All right, come on, let's move. Move!

21:47.547 --> 21:55.821
♪

21:55.846 --> 21:58.926
[MONITOR BEEPING]

21:59.125 --> 22:01.289
Hey, you look like someone
I used to work with.

22:01.314 --> 22:04.482
Thank you for letting me do this.

22:04.507 --> 22:07.261
Hello, everyone. I'm Maggie Pierce.

22:07.286 --> 22:10.768
I'm Chief of Cardiothoracic
at Grey-Sloan Memorial.

22:10.793 --> 22:12.831
Don't hold that against me.

22:12.856 --> 22:14.324
Who is ready to take on

22:14.349 --> 22:17.345
the biggest biatrial myxoma

22:17.370 --> 22:19.393
- I have ever seen?
- This isn't gonna work

22:19.418 --> 22:21.477
if she doesn't know everyone's listening.

22:21.502 --> 22:24.637
- [CHEERS AND APPLAUSE]
- All right! That's better.

22:24.662 --> 22:26.106
Okay, folks, best behavior.

22:26.131 --> 22:28.189
If we impress Pierce, she just might come

22:28.214 --> 22:30.052
and run cardio for us.

22:31.186 --> 22:32.863
You know that's never
gonna happen, right?

22:32.888 --> 22:34.564
You'd be surprised
how many times it's worked.

22:34.589 --> 22:35.838
Hmm.

22:36.575 --> 22:38.634
Shout if you need anything.

22:38.659 --> 22:40.439
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

22:40.464 --> 22:41.724
Scalpel.

22:41.756 --> 22:50.828
♪

22:50.853 --> 22:55.793
♪

22:55.818 --> 22:57.135
♪

23:02.527 --> 23:05.284
I'm sorry if I raised my voice earlier.

23:06.528 --> 23:08.725
Maggie really is the best there is.

23:08.750 --> 23:11.040
Sabi couldn't be in better hands.

23:11.424 --> 23:13.760
Last time you tried to calm
my nerves in a waiting room,

23:13.785 --> 23:15.419
Mom died.

23:15.495 --> 23:17.645
I was 10 years old, Chris.

23:23.364 --> 23:25.144
No signal here.

23:25.169 --> 23:26.730
I need to call the family.

23:26.755 --> 23:28.102
WOMAN ON P.A.: Dr. Sykes...

23:28.127 --> 23:29.908
Dr. Jennifer Sykes, call Recovery.

23:29.933 --> 23:31.596
Dr. Sykes, call Recovery.

23:35.127 --> 23:38.435
Hey, Richard. What's wrong?

23:38.460 --> 23:41.664
- N-Not now, Gemma, please.
- Oh, we go back too far back

23:41.689 --> 23:44.131
for me to leave you alone
looking like this.

23:44.156 --> 23:46.666
What is it? You need a meeting?

23:46.691 --> 23:48.160
Um...

23:48.185 --> 23:51.945
Maggie's operating on my niece right now.

23:51.970 --> 23:55.070
She came out here
for the first time in years.

23:55.095 --> 23:56.355
Her father, too.

23:56.380 --> 23:57.598
For my help.

23:57.623 --> 24:00.411
I thought they wanted
nothing to do with Maggie.

24:00.436 --> 24:02.258
My brother and sister, yes, but...

24:02.925 --> 24:05.990
Sabi, she's not like them.

24:06.015 --> 24:07.726
She's welcoming

24:07.751 --> 24:10.643
and forgiving

24:10.668 --> 24:13.185
and kind...

24:13.210 --> 24:15.604
and I turned my back on her.

24:16.829 --> 24:19.339
Family's complicated. [CHUCKLES]

24:19.364 --> 24:21.179
I know. I keep saying that.

24:21.204 --> 24:23.737
But I feel like it's just an excuse now.

24:24.918 --> 24:28.470
You made a sincere attempt at amends.

24:28.495 --> 24:30.477
If the other person
doesn't want to hear it,

24:30.502 --> 24:31.790
that's not on you.

24:31.815 --> 24:34.776
They aren't wrong.

24:34.854 --> 24:36.322
I did think I was better.

24:36.347 --> 24:38.706
Or at least knew better.

24:40.174 --> 24:43.621
You know, I never understood
why they were so content

24:43.646 --> 24:45.801
staying in their small, little world.

24:46.598 --> 24:48.135
You know what Chris said to me

24:48.160 --> 24:49.930
when I told him I was an alcoholic?

24:51.076 --> 24:53.058
"That's what you get."

24:53.993 --> 24:56.603
Like ambition was to blame.

24:56.628 --> 24:58.373
Like everything would've been fine

24:58.398 --> 25:01.692
if I hadn't gotten
a big head and left home.

25:03.011 --> 25:04.792
I'm sorry, Richard.

25:04.817 --> 25:06.251
[SIGHS]

25:06.276 --> 25:11.494
♪

25:11.519 --> 25:12.605
[SIGHS]

25:12.630 --> 25:13.636
♪

25:13.661 --> 25:15.122
Richard?

25:15.989 --> 25:17.109
Catherine.

25:17.134 --> 25:19.921
Uh, oh, well, this is Gemma.

25:19.946 --> 25:21.936
Uh, she's a friend.

25:21.961 --> 25:23.297
I can see that.

25:23.322 --> 25:25.207
It's so good to meet you, Catherine.

25:25.232 --> 25:28.344
I've heard a-a lot about you, and, um...

25:29.420 --> 25:31.862
- Well, I'll let... I'll let you two be.
- Yeah.

25:31.887 --> 25:35.373
♪

25:35.394 --> 25:37.348
Um...

25:37.373 --> 25:39.675
I wasn't sure you'd come. [CHUCKLES]

25:39.700 --> 25:41.591
Of course I came.

25:41.616 --> 25:42.945
It's family.

25:42.970 --> 25:44.404
♪

25:44.429 --> 25:46.001
CHRIS: Vanessa's making calls.

25:46.026 --> 25:47.703
Starting a prayer chain.

25:47.728 --> 25:49.615
♪

25:49.640 --> 25:51.039
Oh, uh, Catherine, you remember Chris.

25:51.064 --> 25:54.441
Of course.
Chris, you must be worried sick.

25:54.466 --> 25:55.922
♪

25:59.160 --> 26:00.769
Once we go on bypass,

26:00.794 --> 26:03.928
I'll make my incision
into the right atrium.

26:03.953 --> 26:05.838
What's her activated clotting time?

26:05.863 --> 26:08.365
ACT shows 300 seconds and rising.

26:08.390 --> 26:09.519
That's good enough to start.

26:09.544 --> 26:11.706
Let's go on pump.

26:11.731 --> 26:13.651
[MONITOR BEEPING]

26:13.676 --> 26:15.525
Clamps off.

26:15.550 --> 26:16.776
Clamp.

26:16.801 --> 26:20.005
[BEEPING CONTINUES]

26:20.030 --> 26:22.540
And so how is Vanessa?

26:22.565 --> 26:23.928
Is she still in that house?

26:23.953 --> 26:25.803
She'll never leave that house.

26:25.828 --> 26:27.053
I did some work for her.

26:27.078 --> 26:28.373
I added a sunroom in the back.

26:28.398 --> 26:30.040
Oh, that sounds lovely.

26:30.065 --> 26:32.747
And the, uh... the... the hardware store?

26:32.772 --> 26:34.762
- It closed last month.
- Oh.

26:34.787 --> 26:36.220
Everyone orders online now.

26:36.245 --> 26:38.060
It closed?

26:38.085 --> 26:39.623
No one told me that.

26:39.648 --> 26:41.324
You didn't ask.

26:41.349 --> 26:43.130
[BREATHES SHARPLY]

26:43.155 --> 26:45.595
So, uh, when was the last time

26:45.620 --> 26:48.268
you all came to visit Seattle?

26:48.293 --> 26:52.261
Well, um, Sabi couldn't have
been more than... what... 8?

26:52.286 --> 26:54.172
Hmm.

26:54.197 --> 26:56.810
W-What was that game
she always wanted to play?

26:56.835 --> 26:57.921
Um...

26:57.946 --> 26:59.484
Papa Never Misses!

26:59.509 --> 27:00.699
The little ones would line up

27:00.724 --> 27:02.817
on one side of the yard,
Chris on the other.

27:02.842 --> 27:04.693
And they would throw him a football

27:04.718 --> 27:06.602
as crazy as they could.

27:06.627 --> 27:10.629
I mean, they would fling it,
and flip it, and spin it.

27:10.654 --> 27:12.540
[CHUCKLING] They'd try
everything to make him miss,

27:12.565 --> 27:13.824
and he never did.

27:13.849 --> 27:14.866
Not once.

27:14.891 --> 27:15.907
Papa Never Misses.

27:15.932 --> 27:17.227
[LAUGHTER]

27:17.252 --> 27:19.172
Sabi came close a few times, though.

27:19.197 --> 27:22.921
Yeah, I remember once
we had a kiddie pool set up,

27:22.946 --> 27:25.371
and Sabi would fill
a little pail of water

27:25.372 --> 27:27.396
and pour it over her cousins' heads,

27:27.421 --> 27:29.652
and they would laugh.

27:29.677 --> 27:31.527
But then, one time, my... my nephew...

27:31.552 --> 27:34.514
W-Was that... Was it Eddie,
Jeffrey, or...?

27:34.539 --> 27:36.562
- It was Eddie.
- [LAUGHS] Yeah, okay.

27:36.587 --> 27:39.201
Her cousin Eddie poured a pail of water

27:39.226 --> 27:40.798
- over Sabi's head.
- Oh.

27:40.823 --> 27:42.881
- Oh, she burst into tears.
- [CHUCKLES]

27:42.906 --> 27:45.069
She came running to me. She said...

27:45.094 --> 27:49.895
[WHIMPERING, STAMMERING] "Uncle Richard,

27:49.920 --> 27:52.778
tell Eddie we don't play like that!"

27:52.803 --> 27:55.971
[LAUGHTER]

27:55.996 --> 27:58.253
- Oh, boy. [CHUCKLES]
- That's Sabi.

27:58.278 --> 28:00.649
Adele loved that story.

28:00.674 --> 28:02.385
[SIGHS]

28:02.410 --> 28:10.203
♪

28:10.228 --> 28:12.296
You got a vending machine around here?

28:12.321 --> 28:14.345
Oh, yeah, down the hall.

28:14.370 --> 28:15.525
Oh, you need some cash?

28:15.558 --> 28:18.136
♪

28:18.161 --> 28:20.429
I can afford a soda, Rich.

28:20.454 --> 28:28.131
♪

28:28.156 --> 28:30.422
Everything I say pisses that man off.

28:30.447 --> 28:32.055
Mm-hmm.

28:32.080 --> 28:34.347
♪

28:34.372 --> 28:37.090
Okay, look, I don't know what
you think you saw, but...

28:37.115 --> 28:38.752
We will talk about that later.

28:38.777 --> 28:41.703
There is nothing to talk about,
Catherine.

28:41.728 --> 28:44.030
Gemma is an accountant here.

28:44.055 --> 28:46.113
A friend from the program.

28:46.138 --> 28:48.857
A while back, she needed a job,
I made some calls.

28:48.882 --> 28:50.974
It was before I even worked here.

28:50.999 --> 28:53.093
I've known her for years.

28:53.118 --> 28:55.442
She was concerned, and that's all.

28:55.826 --> 28:58.162
You're talking an awful lot
for someone who says

28:58.187 --> 29:00.836
there's nothing to talk about.

29:00.861 --> 29:02.266
[TAB POPS]

29:02.810 --> 29:04.626
I need some fresh air.

29:04.651 --> 29:06.605
♪

29:06.630 --> 29:09.278
[DOOR OPENS]

29:09.303 --> 29:11.176
- [SIGHS]
- [DOOR CLOSES]

29:11.989 --> 29:13.839
[QUIETLY] Doctors made Mommy
all better, Bub.

29:13.864 --> 29:15.714
I'm so sorry I scared you.

29:15.739 --> 29:17.276
I love you so much.

29:17.301 --> 29:19.985
And when I'm all better,
we're gonna go to the zoo.

29:20.010 --> 29:21.408
Can we see the baby giraffes?

29:21.433 --> 29:22.832
Yes, anything you want.

29:22.857 --> 29:25.193
Okay? But right now, Mommy's
got to rest a little bit.

29:25.218 --> 29:26.721
All right?

29:26.746 --> 29:28.584
[MONITOR BEEPING]

29:33.727 --> 29:35.751
I got so lucky with Henry.

29:35.776 --> 29:37.437
He's such a good kid...

29:37.437 --> 29:39.461
You know, he's so happy, even
with the little I can give him,

29:39.486 --> 29:41.579
and he does not deserve less.

29:41.604 --> 29:43.316
Of course not.

29:43.341 --> 29:46.225
And you don't have to explain
that to anyone.

29:46.225 --> 29:47.484
It is your decision,

29:47.509 --> 29:49.985
even if you didn't have Henry
or money problems.

29:50.010 --> 29:51.200
[BREATHES SHARPLY]

29:51.225 --> 29:53.284
[BEEPING CONTINUES]

29:53.309 --> 29:55.991
All right, Cassidy, the doctors
said the labs and imaging

29:56.016 --> 29:59.221
showed an eight-week pregnancy,
so you're all clear.

29:59.246 --> 30:01.026
Okay, so that's it? It's just the pill?

30:01.051 --> 30:02.485
Two pills, actually.

30:02.510 --> 30:04.603
You'll take one medication now
to block the hormones

30:04.628 --> 30:05.957
that keep the pregnancy viable,

30:05.981 --> 30:07.589
then a second pill in 24 hours

30:07.614 --> 30:09.318
to help contract the uterus.

30:09.319 --> 30:11.308
You'll feel nauseated and crampy,

30:11.333 --> 30:14.051
probably emotional... because hormones.
Okay.

30:14.076 --> 30:16.516
And it will be difficult when
you're passing the tissue.

30:16.541 --> 30:18.565
A lot of doctors say
it's like a heavy period,

30:18.590 --> 30:19.884
but it's more than that.

30:19.909 --> 30:21.030
It's completely safe.

30:21.055 --> 30:22.975
I just want you to be prepared.

30:23.000 --> 30:24.768
[CHUCKLES] Thank you.

30:27.990 --> 30:29.736
You'll need to schedule
an appointment with an OB

30:29.761 --> 30:31.126
in about a week or so

30:31.151 --> 30:32.792
to confirm that the medication worked

30:32.817 --> 30:34.667
and that there's no infection.

30:34.692 --> 30:36.820
Thank you. Thank you so much.

30:36.845 --> 30:39.216
I'm so grateful to both of you.

30:39.241 --> 30:41.785
Looks like Dr. Hunt is here
to do some post-op work,

30:41.810 --> 30:43.278
so get some rest, Cassidy.

30:43.303 --> 30:45.778
And you have my card
if you need anything.

30:45.803 --> 30:49.880
♪

30:49.905 --> 30:51.686
[SIREN WAILS IN DISTANCE]

30:51.711 --> 30:54.219
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

30:54.244 --> 30:56.477
Oh, hey.

30:56.502 --> 30:57.936
Any news?

30:57.961 --> 30:59.591
Still in surgery.

31:00.074 --> 31:02.375
- I'll say another prayer.
- Mm.

31:02.400 --> 31:05.778
Richard tells me you're quite gifted.

31:05.803 --> 31:06.855
Pardon?

31:06.880 --> 31:09.389
With numbers.
You work in accounting, right?

31:09.414 --> 31:11.820
- Oh. [CHUCKLES] Yes.
- Mm.

31:11.845 --> 31:14.250
You know, at the Fox Foundation,
we're always looking

31:14.275 --> 31:16.230
for people we can trust

31:16.255 --> 31:18.667
- with our finances.
- Oh.

31:18.692 --> 31:20.507
There's a lot of opportunity.

31:20.532 --> 31:22.694
I'm sure it pays better than this place.

31:22.719 --> 31:25.333
[CHUCKLES] You're too kind.

31:25.358 --> 31:27.764
Any friend of Richard's...

31:27.789 --> 31:29.778
Give him a résumé.

31:29.803 --> 31:31.514
Okay. Maybe I will.

31:31.539 --> 31:32.555
You should.

31:32.580 --> 31:35.507
We have openings all over the country,

31:35.532 --> 31:38.355
though none here in Seattle, I'm afraid.

31:38.380 --> 31:41.371
[SIGHS]
I should be getting back inside.

31:41.396 --> 31:42.585
Have a good night.

31:42.610 --> 31:45.016
♪

31:45.041 --> 31:46.058
[FOOTSTEPS DEPARTING]

31:46.083 --> 31:49.253
[SIREN WAILING IN DISTANCE]

31:49.278 --> 31:52.912
Okay, I've dissected most of the tumor

31:52.937 --> 31:54.266
from the right atrium.

31:54.313 --> 31:55.607
Suction.

31:55.632 --> 31:56.788
[ALARMS BLARING]

31:56.813 --> 31:57.899
MAPs are dropping.

31:57.924 --> 31:59.323
The bypass circuit is clotting off.

31:59.348 --> 32:00.503
Damn it, she's clotting.

32:00.528 --> 32:01.683
Why is she clotting?!

32:01.708 --> 32:03.456
What is her ACT now? 370 seconds.

32:03.456 --> 32:04.716
What?!

32:04.741 --> 32:07.390
You said it was 300 and rising
before we started.

32:07.415 --> 32:09.507
It should be over 480 by now.

32:09.532 --> 32:10.931
We could've given her more heparin.

32:10.956 --> 32:12.736
She's been dosed multiple times
with heparin.

32:12.761 --> 32:14.403
Why didn't you tell me
she had stopped rising?

32:14.428 --> 32:16.001
Our cardio doctor always asks.

32:16.026 --> 32:17.910
It's protocol. You never asked.

32:17.910 --> 32:19.691
Okay, she's heparin-resistant.

32:19.716 --> 32:21.461
Her blood doesn't clot like normal.

32:21.486 --> 32:23.128
Her pressure's gone.

32:23.153 --> 32:24.968
Okay, everyone stop and listen to me!

32:24.993 --> 32:26.739
We have three minutes
before we lose this patient

32:26.764 --> 32:27.989
from lack of blood flow.

32:28.014 --> 32:30.107
We need a new bypass machine and pumps,

32:30.132 --> 32:31.601
ice to keep her body cool,

32:31.601 --> 32:32.966
and start FFP.

32:32.991 --> 32:34.528
Let's move! Clamps!

32:34.553 --> 32:36.125
[ALARMS BLARING]

32:36.150 --> 32:40.292
♪

32:40.317 --> 32:42.375
Come on. Come on.

32:42.400 --> 32:43.486
Stay with me.

32:43.511 --> 32:48.765
♪

32:48.789 --> 32:51.635
Amelia. You crossed a line.

32:51.635 --> 32:53.590
She needed help
that you wouldn't give her.

32:53.614 --> 32:55.256
You don't work here.

32:55.281 --> 32:57.269
Well, from what I've heard,
most of the people who do

32:57.294 --> 32:58.980
lack the skill and sensitivity
that I have,

32:58.980 --> 33:01.074
so you could just say thank you.

33:01.099 --> 33:02.984
Owen, did you really want
to force that poor mom

33:03.008 --> 33:05.241
to bring another human being
onto the planet against her will,

33:05.266 --> 33:07.080
or did you refuse her an abortion

33:07.105 --> 33:08.817
because I wanted to help her have one?

33:08.842 --> 33:10.310
You don't get to come to my place of work

33:10.334 --> 33:11.733
and order me around, okay?

33:11.758 --> 33:13.469
[DOOR SLAMS]

33:13.469 --> 33:15.492
I didn't order you around.

33:15.517 --> 33:18.167
I ordered her an OB
who ordered her some pills!

33:18.192 --> 33:21.534
And you're angry with me for
reasons I can't quite ascertain.

33:21.559 --> 33:24.313
So you said no to her because I said yes.

33:24.338 --> 33:25.903
I said no to her because...

33:25.904 --> 33:27.442
'cause sometimes
people change their minds,

33:27.467 --> 33:28.831
and she was traumatized by a fall.

33:28.856 --> 33:30.358
A fall that she took accidentally

33:30.383 --> 33:32.580
after intentionally trying
to abort the fetus.

33:32.605 --> 33:35.809
You think that the trauma would
change her mind?

33:35.834 --> 33:38.132
Is this about me?!
Is this because I'm pregnant?

33:38.133 --> 33:40.434
So you think that women who say
that they don't want babies

33:40.459 --> 33:43.421
are gonna just wake up one day
and change their minds?

33:44.284 --> 33:45.579
Amelia, that's absurd.

33:45.604 --> 33:47.038
I agree. She was clear.

33:47.063 --> 33:48.322
She knew what she wanted.

33:48.347 --> 33:49.746
She was not gonna change her mind.

33:49.771 --> 33:52.281
And for the record, I did not
change my mind, either.

33:52.306 --> 33:55.266
I... I just got pregnant, and I exercised

33:55.291 --> 33:57.385
my freedom of choice to not
have an abortion.

33:57.386 --> 33:58.837
That's right. So you didn't want
to have kids,

33:58.862 --> 34:00.191
but now you're with
somebody else, and you do.

34:00.216 --> 34:01.476
Y-You're... You're perfectly happy

34:01.501 --> 34:03.942
now that you're having a baby
with another man!

34:04.276 --> 34:06.856
You and I broke up twice.

34:06.881 --> 34:10.050
- Once when we got divorced and then...
- Yeah. Yeah, we got divorced.

34:10.074 --> 34:11.619
You remember why we got divorced?

34:11.643 --> 34:13.077
You remember the pain
that you put me through

34:13.101 --> 34:14.928
when you told me that you
didn't want to ever have kids?

34:14.953 --> 34:17.150
That you didn't want to ever be a mother?

34:17.176 --> 34:19.081
That pain, that "truth," Amelia, it...

34:20.489 --> 34:22.132
It ended our marriage.

34:22.157 --> 34:23.520
And now you're telling me
that it's not because

34:23.545 --> 34:25.257
you didn't want to have kids, you just...

34:25.282 --> 34:27.299
[SIGHS]

34:27.496 --> 34:29.799
You didn't want to have them with me.

34:29.824 --> 34:32.159
♪

34:32.185 --> 34:33.862
Owen.

34:33.887 --> 34:40.536
♪

34:40.562 --> 34:42.864
Uh, I gotta, um...

34:42.889 --> 34:47.192
♪

34:49.196 --> 34:52.088
Amelia. Amelia, wait. Wait.

34:52.112 --> 34:53.130
Owen. [SIGHS]

34:53.155 --> 34:55.034
I'm sorry.

34:55.898 --> 34:58.204
It's my turn to apologize.

34:59.265 --> 35:01.081
I should have thought this through.

35:01.106 --> 35:02.747
I should not have ambushed you

35:02.772 --> 35:04.171
at your place of employment.

35:04.196 --> 35:05.594
I should've known that this was gonna be

35:05.619 --> 35:08.742
a bigger conversation, and I'm sorry.

35:14.231 --> 35:17.182
When I told you
that I didn't want kids...

35:18.415 --> 35:20.057
I didn't.

35:20.082 --> 35:22.591
I didn't when we started seeing
each other and you had Leo.

35:22.616 --> 35:24.084
I didn't when Betty showed up.

35:24.109 --> 35:26.133
If I'm honest,
I didn't even know for sure

35:26.158 --> 35:28.204
when I found out I was pregnant.

35:29.699 --> 35:31.932
But something changed. [SIGHS]

35:31.957 --> 35:34.535
What we went through with Leo and Betty

35:34.560 --> 35:36.272
is a big part of that.

35:36.297 --> 35:38.119
I wasn't ready before.

35:39.144 --> 35:40.580
I am now.

35:41.443 --> 35:44.010
And I have you to thank for that.

35:46.256 --> 35:48.338
Like it or not, we're family now.

35:49.245 --> 35:50.458
I like it.

35:53.122 --> 35:54.937
I always liked it.

35:54.962 --> 35:57.438
[ROO PANES' "COMMENTATOR" PLAYS]

35:57.463 --> 36:02.646
♪

36:02.671 --> 36:04.347
- [HUMMING]
- Mm.

36:04.372 --> 36:07.842
So, okay, how are we gonna do
this whole family thing?

36:07.867 --> 36:09.232
'Cause there's a lot of us.

36:09.257 --> 36:13.433
There's me, Teddy, you, Link,
Leo, Allison, and...

36:13.458 --> 36:15.378
- you got a name yet?
- Uh...

36:15.403 --> 36:17.321
W-We literally have nothing.

36:17.346 --> 36:18.537
And I don't know how this works.

36:18.562 --> 36:19.787
I mean, there should be a book...

36:19.812 --> 36:21.697
Like, "What to Expect
When You're Expecting,

36:21.722 --> 36:24.753
But You Already Sort of Have
an Adopted Kid with Your Ex..."

36:24.778 --> 36:27.359
"...Who Just Had a Baby
with His, uh, Soul Mate."

36:27.384 --> 36:30.068
- Sounds like a bestseller.
- [LAUGHS]

36:30.680 --> 36:32.215
[SIGHS]

36:32.519 --> 36:37.016
♪ She was like the wind in your hair ♪

36:37.041 --> 36:39.829
I was really terrible
with my patient, so I should...

36:39.854 --> 36:43.518
Yeah, you should bring her
an extra Jell-O, for sure.

36:43.543 --> 36:44.838
[CHUCKLES]

36:44.863 --> 36:46.677
Maybe one for Henry.

36:46.702 --> 36:48.379
- [CHUCKLING] Yeah.
- ♪ Just like the freshest air ♪

36:48.404 --> 36:50.116
♪ Ooh, ooh, ooh, ooh ♪

36:50.141 --> 36:52.927
♪ Whoo, ooh, ooh, ooh,
ooh, ooh, ooh, ooh ♪

36:52.952 --> 36:56.574
♪ Ooh, ooh, ooh, ooh, ooh ♪

36:56.599 --> 36:59.367
♪ Whoo, ooh, ooh, ooh,
ooh, ooh, ooh, ooh, ♪

36:59.392 --> 37:01.450
- Is this normal?
- ♪ Ooh, ooh, ooh, ooh, ohh ♪

37:01.475 --> 37:03.012
- For it to take this long?
- ♪ Ooh, ooh, ooh, ooh ♪

37:03.037 --> 37:05.235
Uh, you don't want to rush
something like this.

37:05.260 --> 37:06.971
♪

37:06.996 --> 37:08.183
♪ Remember... ♪

37:08.208 --> 37:09.780
I can't imagine
what you're going through.

37:09.805 --> 37:12.142
- No, you can't.
- ♪ ...when I used to say ♪

37:12.167 --> 37:13.794
Look, what I mean was that...

37:13.819 --> 37:15.429
♪ You never took your
shoes off at the door? ♪

37:15.454 --> 37:17.927
I've only known Maggie a few years.

37:18.351 --> 37:21.277
But in that time,
I've grown to care about her

37:21.302 --> 37:23.846
more than any person I've ever known.

37:23.871 --> 37:25.548
I worry about her future,

37:25.573 --> 37:28.283
- her safety, her happiness.
- ♪ Well, love ♪

37:28.296 --> 37:31.153
- If I loved her any more...
- ♪ I just want you to know ♪

37:31.178 --> 37:32.855
...I'm not sure I could bear it.

37:32.880 --> 37:34.347
♪ How I miss your running commentary ♪

37:34.372 --> 37:37.819
And it's a fraction of what
you must be feeling right now.

37:37.844 --> 37:39.213
♪ Beside me... ♪

37:39.238 --> 37:40.806
I'm sorry.

37:40.831 --> 37:43.062
♪ ...is an empty seat ♪

37:43.087 --> 37:45.737
♪

37:45.761 --> 37:50.423
♪ You got me wondering ♪

37:50.448 --> 37:54.351
♪ All the things you're thinking ♪

37:54.376 --> 37:56.990
MAGGIE: It's all clotted!
Everything has clotted!

37:57.015 --> 37:59.059
Suction! Start the pump!

37:59.084 --> 38:00.900
I'm trying. Still no flow.

38:00.925 --> 38:03.156
We need to get oxygen to her brain!

38:03.181 --> 38:04.407
How long has the circuit been down?

38:04.432 --> 38:05.865
I can get her back! I can.

38:05.890 --> 38:07.219
- How long?
- Seven minutes.

38:07.244 --> 38:08.857
I connected bypass in time.

38:08.882 --> 38:11.218
There's just too many clots.
We need some more ice!

38:11.243 --> 38:12.538
We need to cool her down some more.

38:12.563 --> 38:13.683
Nuce, seven minutes is too long.

38:13.708 --> 38:15.385
We can get her back! We can get her back!

38:15.410 --> 38:17.122
Her entire circulation has clotted off.

38:17.147 --> 38:18.614
There's no way she can recover from that.

38:18.639 --> 38:20.003
- Come on.
- All right? She's gone.

38:20.028 --> 38:22.260
- Come on, come on, come on.
- Okay, everybody stop!

38:22.285 --> 38:24.170
Not yet, Alex. Not yet.

38:24.195 --> 38:25.455
- Maggie...
- No, no!

38:25.480 --> 38:27.573
...she's brain dead. Let her go.

38:27.598 --> 38:29.066
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

38:29.091 --> 38:36.358
♪ Ohh, ohh ♪

38:36.383 --> 38:38.338
- [BREATHING SHAKILY]
- Time of death, 18:58.

38:38.363 --> 38:40.491
♪ Well, thank you
for this whole surprise ♪

38:40.516 --> 38:42.644
♪ I have been alive ♪

38:42.669 --> 38:44.693
♪ I have been alive ♪

38:44.718 --> 38:46.811
♪ I have been alive ♪

38:46.836 --> 38:48.929
♪ I have been alive ♪

38:48.954 --> 38:53.755
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

38:53.780 --> 38:55.804
[CELLPHONE VIBRATES]

38:55.829 --> 38:57.991
[SIGHS]

38:58.016 --> 39:00.098
[CELLPHONE VIBRATES]

39:08.901 --> 39:11.028
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

39:11.053 --> 39:13.285
- I can't do this.
- I'll be with you.

39:13.310 --> 39:15.770
No, no, no, Alex,
I can't do this. I can't.

39:15.795 --> 39:17.263
I can't. I can't. They... They...

39:17.288 --> 39:19.763
They didn't want me to operate.

39:19.788 --> 39:22.298
They told me not to, and I pushed them.

39:22.323 --> 39:24.485
I bullied them.

39:24.510 --> 39:26.013
I told them I was the best.

39:26.038 --> 39:27.124
You are.

39:27.149 --> 39:29.659
Alex, I-I can't... I can't tell them.

39:29.684 --> 39:32.148
- Come on.
- [BREATHING SHAKILY]

39:38.871 --> 39:40.999
You lost your patient.

39:41.024 --> 39:42.701
You tried to do all the right things,

39:42.726 --> 39:44.854
but you lost your patient.

39:44.879 --> 39:46.277
And you're blaming yourself, and...

39:46.302 --> 39:48.912
and I can't make you not feel that.

39:49.111 --> 39:51.239
But you have to tell them.

39:51.264 --> 39:54.364
So just stand here, get it
all out of your system,

39:54.389 --> 39:56.878
and then pull yourself
back together again.

39:57.535 --> 39:58.922
Get it out.

40:00.178 --> 40:01.716
[CRYING]

40:02.630 --> 40:09.098
[SOBBING]

40:09.123 --> 40:11.768
MEREDITH: Grace under pressure.

40:11.835 --> 40:15.005
One clumsy word, one careless gesture

40:15.030 --> 40:17.227
can cause irreparable harm.

40:17.252 --> 40:26.741
♪

40:26.766 --> 40:31.659
♪

40:35.647 --> 40:37.289
H-How is she?

40:37.314 --> 40:38.817
Is she okay?

40:38.842 --> 40:40.396
- Can I see her?
- [DOOR CLOSES]

40:42.621 --> 40:44.124
I'm Alex Karev. I'm the Chief.

40:44.149 --> 40:45.478
Would you, uh, like to sit down?

40:45.503 --> 40:47.493
I'm fine standing.

40:47.917 --> 40:49.597
So, focus on facts.

40:49.622 --> 40:50.951
What happened?

40:50.976 --> 40:53.728
What was the problem,
and what did you do?

40:53.753 --> 40:55.847
Don't make it personal.

40:55.872 --> 40:58.208
During surgery, we discovered

40:58.233 --> 41:01.923
that Sabrina has a resistance to heparin,

41:01.948 --> 41:03.462
- so her blood...
- W-What's that?

41:03.487 --> 41:04.504
W-What's heparin?

41:04.529 --> 41:06.781
Uh, it's a drug to prevent clotting.

41:08.213 --> 41:10.271
Which didn't work for her.

41:10.296 --> 41:14.194
So during surgery,
her blood began to clot,

41:14.219 --> 41:16.451
and that clogged the bypass machine,

41:16.476 --> 41:20.652
which meant we had to
change machines mid-surgery.

41:20.677 --> 41:22.505
I-I don't understand.

41:22.530 --> 41:24.138
So you had to stop?

41:24.168 --> 41:25.323
Is she okay?

41:25.348 --> 41:27.441
Answer questions directly.

41:27.466 --> 41:29.906
This is not your loss.

41:29.931 --> 41:31.531
This is not your pain.

41:31.786 --> 41:33.602
Never make it about you.

41:33.627 --> 41:35.893
Sabrina's condition was critical

41:35.918 --> 41:39.480
before we ever got to the operating room.

41:40.344 --> 41:43.408
I did everything that I could,

41:43.433 --> 41:44.861
but, unfortunately,

41:45.865 --> 41:48.062
I couldn't save her.

41:48.087 --> 41:50.658
- [EXHALES SHARPLY]
- She died.

41:51.558 --> 41:53.964
Oh, Maggie...

41:53.989 --> 41:56.603
CHRIS: No.

41:56.628 --> 41:57.888
No, no, no, no. no.

41:57.987 --> 41:59.871
[JEFFREY AMOR'S "TOO MUCH" PLAYS]

41:59.896 --> 42:01.461
Sabi?

42:01.486 --> 42:03.718
♪ Underneath it all ♪

42:03.938 --> 42:05.337
No.

42:05.362 --> 42:08.358
And if there's no silver
lining, don't make one up.

42:08.383 --> 42:10.684
Your job isn't to make
the bad news sound better.

42:10.709 --> 42:12.663
- Chris, let's get you out of here.
- Get your hands off me!

42:12.688 --> 42:14.364
Okay, now.

42:14.389 --> 42:17.038
- I didn't even want her to operate!
- ♪ Tell me it's not real ♪

42:17.063 --> 42:19.200
Sabrina didn't!

42:19.225 --> 42:20.589
♪ I know it is, but... ♪

42:20.614 --> 42:22.047
You didn't listen!

42:22.072 --> 42:24.792
♪ ...I'd rather just pretend ♪

42:24.817 --> 42:26.147
Even though you're in pain, too...

42:26.172 --> 42:28.238
- ♪ And feel your heartbeat
next to mine ♪ - [DOOR SLAMS]

42:28.263 --> 42:30.977
...even though you don't
feel like a doctor...

42:31.002 --> 42:33.076
Maggie, is... is she cleaned up?

42:33.101 --> 42:36.097
- Can we see her?
- ♪ One last time ♪

42:36.122 --> 42:38.352
Come on, Richard. Richard, come on.
Get your brother.

42:38.377 --> 42:41.876
We got to go help him call
the rest of the family.

42:42.510 --> 42:45.019
You're just another person, alone,

42:45.020 --> 42:46.628
falling into the dark.

42:46.653 --> 42:52.067
♪
